{
  "texts": [
    "Yoon et al. [147] use a data refinement approach to improve the robustness of one-class classification model.",
    "Qiu et al. [148] propose a strategy for training an anomaly detector in the presence of unlabeled anomalies, which is compatible with a broad class of models.",
    "They create labelled anomalies synthetically and jointly optimize the loss function with normal data and synthesis abnormal data.",
    "Chen et al. [149] introduce an interpolated Gaussian descriptor that learns a one-class Gaussian anomaly classifier trained with adversarially interpolated training samples.",
    "However, the majority of the aforementioned approaches have not been verified on real industrial image datasets."
  ]
}